verses.text_plain: And it came to pass in those days, when there was no king in Israel, that there was a certain Levite sojourning on the side of mount Ephraim, who took to him a concubine out of Beth–lehem–judah.
verses.verse_html:
1And it came to pass in those days, when there was no king in Israel, that there was a certain Levite sojourning on the side of mount Ephraim, who took to him a concubine out of Beth–lehem–judah. ▼
▼ a concubine: Heb. a woman a concubine, or, a wife a concubine

tokens.text: And it came to pass in those days

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a concubine: Heb. a woman a concubine, or, a wife a concubine
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a concubine: Heb. a woman a concubine, or, a wife a concubine

verses.text_plain: And his concubine played the whore against him, and went away from him unto her father’s house to Beth–lehem–judah, and was there four whole months.
verses.verse_html:
2And his concubine played the whore against him, and went away from him unto her father’s house to Beth–lehem–judah, and was there four whole months. ▼
▼ four whole months: or, a year and four month: Heb. days, four months

footnotes.body_text: ▼ four whole months: or, a year and four month: Heb. days, four months
footnotes.body_html: ▼ four whole months: or, a year and four month: Heb. days, four months

verses.text_plain: And her husband arose, and went after her, to speak friendly unto her, and to bring her again, having his servant with him, and a couple of asses: and she brought him into her father’s house: and when the father of the damsel saw him, he rejoiced to meet him.
verses.verse_html:
3And her husband arose, and went after her, to speak friendly unto her, and to bring her again, having his servant with him, and a couple of asses: and she brought him into her father’s house: and when the father of the damsel saw him, he rejoiced to meet him. ▼
▼ friendly…: Heb. to her heart

footnotes.body_html: ▼ friendly…: Heb. to her heart

verses.text_plain: And his father in law, the damsel’s father, retained him; and he abode with him three days: so they did eat and drink, and lodged there.
verses.verse_html: 4And his father in law, the damsel’s father, retained him; and he abode with him three days: so they did eat and drink, and lodged there.

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass on the fourth day, when they arose early in the morning, that he rose up to depart: and the damsel’s father said unto his son in law, Comfort thine heart with a morsel of bread, and afterward go your way.
verses.verse_html:
5And it came to pass on the fourth day, when they arose early in the morning, that he rose up to depart: and the damsel’s father said unto his son in law, Comfort thine heart with a morsel of bread, and afterward go your way. ▼
▼ Comfort: Heb. Strengthen

tokens.text: And it came to pass on the fourth

verses.text_plain: And they sat down, and did eat and drink both of them together: for the damsel’s father had said unto the man, Be content, I pray thee, and tarry all night, and let thine heart be merry.
verses.verse_html: 6And they sat down, and did eat and drink both of them together: for the damsel’s father had said unto the man, Be content, I pray thee, and tarry all night, and let thine heart be merry.

tokens.text: I pray thee, and tarry all night

verses.text_plain: And when the man rose up to depart, his father in law urged him: therefore he lodged there again.
verses.verse_html: 7And when the man rose up to depart, his father in law urged him: therefore he lodged there again.

verses.text_plain: And he arose early in the morning on the fifth day to depart: and the damsel’s father said, Comfort thine heart, I pray thee. And they tarried until afternoon, and they did eat both of them.
verses.verse_html:
8And he arose early in the morning on the fifth day to depart: and the damsel’s father said, Comfort thine heart, I pray thee. And they tarried until afternoon, and they did eat both of them. ▼
▼ until afternoon: Heb. till the day declined

tokens.text: I pray thee. And they tarried

footnotes.body_text: ▼ until afternoon: Heb. till the day declined
footnotes.body_html: ▼ until afternoon: Heb. till the day declined

verses.text_plain: And when the man rose up to depart, he, and his concubine, and his servant, his father in law, the damsel’s father, said unto him, Behold, now the day draweth toward evening, I pray you tarry all night: behold, the day groweth to an end, lodge here, that thine heart may be merry; and to morrow get you early on your way, that thou mayest go home.
verses.verse_html:
9And when the man rose up to depart, he, and his concubine, and his servant, his father in law, the damsel’s father, said unto him, Behold, now the day draweth toward evening, I pray you tarry all night: behold, the day groweth to an end, lodge here, that thine heart may be merry; and to morrow get you early on your way, that thou mayest go home. ▼
▼ draweth: Heb. is weak
 , ▼
▼ the day groweth to an end: Heb. it is the pitching time of the day
 , ▼

verses.text_plain: But the man would not tarry that night, but he rose up and departed, and came over against Jebus, which is Jerusalem; and there were with him two asses saddled, his concubine also was with him.
verses.verse_html:
10But the man would not tarry that night, but he rose up and departed, and came over against Jebus, which is Jerusalem; and there were with him two asses saddled, his concubine also was with him. ▼
▼ over against: Heb. to over against

footnotes.body_text: ▼ over against: Heb. to over against
footnotes.body_html: ▼ over against: Heb. to over against

verses.text_plain: And when they were by Jebus, the day was far spent; and the servant said unto his master, Come, I pray thee, and let us turn in into this city of the Jebusites, and lodge in it.
verses.verse_html: 11And when they were by Jebus, the day was far spent; and the servant said unto his master, Come, I pray thee, and let us turn in into this city of the Jebusites, and lodge in it.

tokens.text: I pray thee, and let us turn in

verses.text_plain: And his master said unto him, We will not turn aside hither into the city of a stranger, that is not of the children of Israel; we will pass over to Gibeah.
verses.verse_html: 12And his master said unto him, We will not turn aside hither into the city of a stranger, that is not of the children of Israel; we will pass over to Gibeah.

tokens.text: unto him, We will not turn aside

verses.text_plain: And he said unto his servant, Come, and let us draw near to one of these places to lodge all night, in Gibeah, or in Ramah.
verses.verse_html: 13And he said unto his servant, Come, and let us draw near to one of these places to lodge all night, in Gibeah, or in Ramah.

verses.text_plain: And they passed on and went their way; and the sun went down upon them when they were by Gibeah, which belongeth to Benjamin.
verses.verse_html: 14And they passed on and went their way; and the sun went down upon them when they were by Gibeah, which belongeth to Benjamin.

verses.text_plain: And they turned aside thither, to go in and to lodge in Gibeah: and when he went in, he sat him down in a street of the city: for there was no man that took them into his house to lodging.
verses.verse_html: 15And they turned aside thither, to go in and to lodge in Gibeah: and when he went in, he sat him down in a street of the city: for there was no man that took them into his house to lodging.

verses.text_plain: And, behold, there came an old man from his work out of the field at even, which was also of mount Ephraim; and he sojourned in Gibeah: but the men of the place were Benjamites.
verses.verse_html: 16And, behold, there came an old man from his work out of the field at even, which was also of mount Ephraim; and he sojourned in Gibeah: but the men of the place were Benjamites.

verses.text_plain: And when he had lifted up his eyes, he saw a wayfaring man in the street of the city: and the old man said, Whither goest thou? and whence comest thou?
verses.verse_html: 17And when he had lifted up his eyes, he saw a wayfaring man in the street of the city: and the old man said, Whither goest thou? and whence comest thou?

tokens.text: And when he had lifted up

verses.text_plain: And he said unto him, We are passing from Beth–lehem–judah toward the side of mount Ephraim; from thence am I: and I went to Beth–lehem–judah, but I am now going to the house of the Lord; and there is no man that receiveth me to house.
verses.verse_html:
18And he said unto him, We are passing from Beth–lehem–judah toward the side of mount Ephraim; from thence am I: and I went to Beth–lehem–judah, but I am now going to the house of the Lord; and there is no man that receiveth me to house. ▼
▼ receiveth: Heb. gathereth

verses.text_plain: Yet there is both straw and provender for our asses; and there is bread and wine also for me, and for thy handmaid, and for the young man which is with thy servants: there is no want of any thing.
verses.verse_html: 19Yet there is both straw and provender for our asses; and there is bread and wine also for me, and for thy handmaid, and for the young man which is with thy servants: there is no want of any thing.

tokens.text: also for me, and for thy handmaid

verses.text_plain: And the old man said, Peace be with thee; howsoever let all thy wants lie upon me; only lodge not in the street.
verses.verse_html: 20And the old man said, Peace be with thee; howsoever let all thy wants lie upon me; only lodge not in the street.

verses.text_plain: So he brought him into his house, and gave provender unto the asses: and they washed their feet, and did eat and drink.
verses.verse_html: 21So he brought him into his house, and gave provender unto the asses: and they washed their feet, and did eat and drink.

verses.text_plain: Now as they were making their hearts merry, behold, the men of the city, certain sons of Belial, beset the house round about, and beat at the door, and spake to the master of the house, the old man, saying, Bring forth the man that came into thine house, that we may know him.
verses.verse_html: 22Now as they were making their hearts merry, behold, the men of the city, certain sons of Belial, beset the house round about, and beat at the door, and spake to the master of the house, the old man, saying, Bring forth the man that came into thine house, that we may know him.

tokens.text: as they were making their hearts

verses.text_plain: And the man, the master of the house, went out unto them, and said unto them, Nay, my brethren, nay, I pray you, do not so wickedly; seeing that this man is come into mine house, do not this folly.
verses.verse_html: 23And the man, the master of the house, went out unto them, and said unto them, Nay, my brethren, nay, I pray you, do not so wickedly; seeing that this man is come into mine house, do not this folly.

verses.text_plain: Behold, here is my daughter a maiden, and his concubine; them I will bring out now, and humble ye them, and do with them what seemeth good unto you: but unto this man do not so vile a thing.
verses.verse_html:
24Behold, here is my daughter a maiden, and his concubine; them I will bring out now, and humble ye them, and do with them what seemeth good unto you: but unto this man do not so vile a thing. ▼
▼ so vile…: Heb. the matter of this folly

tokens.text: unto you: but unto this man

footnotes.body_text: ▼ so vile…: Heb. the matter of this folly
footnotes.body_html: ▼ so vile…: Heb. the matter of this folly

verses.text_plain: But the men would not hearken to him: so the man took his concubine, and brought her forth unto them; and they knew her, and abused her all the night until the morning: and when the day began to spring, they let her go.
verses.verse_html: 25But the men would not hearken to him: so the man took his concubine, and brought her forth unto them; and they knew her, and abused her all the night until the morning: and when the day began to spring, they let her go.

verses.text_plain: Then came the woman in the dawning of the day, and fell down at the door of the man’s house where her lord was, till it was light.
verses.verse_html: 26Then came the woman in the dawning of the day, and fell down at the door of the man’s house where her lord was, till it was light.

verses.text_plain: And her lord rose up in the morning, and opened the doors of the house, and went out to go his way: and, behold, the woman his concubine was fallen down at the door of the house, and her hands were upon the threshold.
verses.verse_html: 27And her lord rose up in the morning, and opened the doors of the house, and went out to go his way: and, behold, the woman his concubine was fallen down at the door of the house, and her hands were upon the threshold.

verses.text_plain: And he said unto her, Up, and let us be going. But none answered. Then the man took her up upon an ass, and the man rose up, and gat him unto his place.
verses.verse_html: 28And he said unto her, Up, and let us be going. But none answered. Then the man took her up upon an ass, and the man rose up, and gat him unto his place.

verses.text_plain: And when he was come into his house, he took a knife, and laid hold on his concubine, and divided her, together with her bones, into twelve pieces, and sent her into all the coasts of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 29And when he was come into his house, he took a knife, and laid hold on his concubine, and divided her, together with her bones, into twelve pieces, and sent her into all the coasts of Israel.

verses.text_plain: And it was so, that all that saw it said, There was no such deed done nor seen from the day that the children of Israel came up out of the land of Egypt unto this day: consider of it, take advice, and speak your minds.
verses.verse_html: 30And it was so, that all that saw it said, There was no such deed done nor seen from the day that the children of Israel came up out of the land of Egypt unto this day: consider of it, take advice, and speak your minds.
